▐▌   ▝▚▄▞▘▐▌ ▐▌▐▙▄▄▀    ▗▄▄▞▘▝▚▄▞▘▐▌ ▐▌▐▌  ▐▌▗▄▄▞▘▝▚▄▞▘▐▌  ▐▌    ▐▙▄▄▖▗▞▘▝▚▖▐▌   ▐▙▄▄▖▐▌ ▐▌▗▄█▄▖▐▌  ▐▌▐▙▄▄▖▐▙▄▄▀
                                                                                                                
The ford johnson algorithm is a sorting algorithm designed to sort with
a minimal amount of comparisons between elements. It was developed by
Lester Randolph Ford Jr. and Selmer Martin Johnson, and published in 1959.

It is also refered to as merge-insertion sort.

Explation of the algorithm :

1)	Devide the elements (keys)  into pairs, leaving one key out if n is odd.
	Call the larger key of the i‑th pair aᵢ and the smaller bᵢ.

	┌─┬─┬─┬─┬─┬─┬─┬─┬─┐
	│8│5│1│4│9│2│6│3│7│
	└─┴─┴─┴─┴─┴─┴─┴─┴─┘
	┌─┬─┐┌─┬─┐┌─┬─┐┌─┬─┐┌─┐
	│5│8││1│4││2│9││3│6││7│
	├─┼─┤├─┼─┤├─┼─┤├─┼─┤├─┤
	│b│a││b│a││b│a││b│a││/│
	└─┴─┘└─┴─┘└─┴─┘└─┴─┘└─┘

	Another way to visualize this is like this:

		┌─┬─┬─┬─┐
	A:	│8│4│9│6│
		└─┴─┴─┴─┘
		 ⬆ ⬆ ⬆ ⬆
		┌─┬─┬─┬─┐┌─┐
	B:	│5│1│2│3││7│
		└─┴─┴─┴─┘└─┘

2) Now repeat this step with the elements in row A making while keeping 
	
		┌─┬─┐┌─┬─┐
	A:	│4│8││6│9│
		└─┴─┘└─┴─┘
		 ⬆ ⬆  ⬆ ⬆
		┌─┬─┐┌─┬─┐┌─┐
	B:	│1│5││3│2││7│
		└─┴─┘└─┴─┘└─┘


		┌─┐┌─┐┌─┐
		│8││9││7│
		└─┘└─┘└─┘
		 ⬆ 	⬆
		┌─┐┌─┐
		│4││6│
		└─┘└─┘
		 ⬆  ⬆
		┌─┐┌─┐
		│5││2│
		└─┘└─┘
		 ⬆ 	⬆
		┌─┐┌─┐
		│1││3│
		└─┘└─┘
